# Purananooru_RAG

**AI-powered Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system** for **Sangam literature**, focused on **Puranānūru poems**.  
This project allows querying, summarizing, and exploring ancient Tamil Sangam poems using modern AI pipelines.

---

## Overview

This project implements a **RAG pipeline** for Sangam texts, particularly **Puranānūru**.  
It leverages:

- **Vector database** for storing embeddings  
- **LLM integration** for generating summaries and explanations  
- **Chunking** and **embedding storage** for efficient retrieval  

Designed for **research, learning, and AI-assisted exploration of Tamil literature**.

---

## Features

- Load and process Sangam texts (`sangam.txt`, `sangam.xlsx`)  
- Generate embeddings for poems and store in vector DB  
- Query poems in Tamil or English using AI  
- Summarize or explain ancient poems in modern English  
- Secure handling of API keys via `.env`  

---

## Example

### Original Tamil Poem:
உரை நூல்:
புறநானூறு – ஔவை துரைசாமி – தமிழ் மண் பதிப்பகம், சென்னை

புறநானூறு 1, பாடியவர்: பெருந்தேவனார், பாடப்பட்டோன்: இறைவன்

கண்ணி கார் நறுங்கொன்றை, காமர்
வண்ண மார்பின் தாருங் கொன்றை;
ஊர்தி வால் வெள் ஏறே, சிறந்த
சீர் கெழு கொடியும் அவ்வேறு என்ப;
...

shell
Copy code

### English Explanation:
Puranānūru 1, Poet Perunthēvanār wrote this many centuries after the Sangam poems.

His kondrai flower strand has rain fragrance. He wears a
kondrai garland on his pretty colored chest. He rides on a
pure white bull and his splendid flag also has the bull.
...

yaml
Copy code

**Notes:**  
This poet also wrote invocation poems for Natrinai, Ainkurunūru, Akanānūru, and Kurunthokai. Puranānūru is the only anthology where these poems are included in the total count.

---

## Quick Start

Clone the repository and install dependencies:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/vijayyy-code/Purananooru_RAG.git
cd Purananooru_RAG
python -m venv venv && venv\Scripts\activate && pip install -r requirements.txt
Linux/Mac users:
source venv/bin/activate instead of venv\Scripts\activate

Set up your .env file (DO NOT commit this):

env
Copy code
API_KEY=your_api_key_here
Usage
Run the main RAG pipeline:

bash
Copy code
python app.py
Other utility scripts:

check.py → verify embeddings

indices_cache.pkl → cached vector indices

sangam.txt / sangam.xlsx → source poems

Folder Structure
bash
Copy code
Purananooru_RAG/
├── venv/                # virtual environment (ignored)
├── .env                 # your API key (ignored)
├── app.py
├── check.py
├── indices_cache.pkl    # cached embeddings
├── requirements.txt
├── sangam.txt
├── sangam.xlsx
